<p>I have set the Rails time zone to 'Moscow' in application.rb.</p>  <p>When I ask for the local time it returns a value that is one hour ahead of the actual local time.</p>  <p>How can I workaround that incorrect time to local conversion?  </p>  <pre><code>2.0.0-p481 :003 &gt; Time.zone  =&gt; #&lt;ActiveSupport::TimeZone:0x000000058a5750 @name="Moscow", @utc_offset=nil, @tzinfo=#&lt;TZInfo::TimezoneProxy: Europe/Moscow&gt;, @current_period=#&lt;TZInfo::TimezonePeriod: #&lt;TZInfo::TimezoneTransitionDefinition: #&lt;TZInfo::TimeOrDateTime: 1301180400&gt;,#&lt;TZInfo::TimezoneOffset: 14400,0,MSK&gt;&gt;,nil&gt;&gt; 2.0.0-p481 :004 &gt; Time.now  =&gt; 2015-09-14 10:37:39 +0000 2.0.0-p481 :005 &gt; Time.current  =&gt; Mon, 14 Sep 2015 14:37:44 MSK +04:00 2.0.0-p481 :006 &gt; tz = TZInfo::Timezone.get('Europe/Moscow')  =&gt; #&lt;TZInfo::DataTimezone: Europe/Moscow&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Here <code>Time.current</code> should return <code>Mon, 14 Sep 2015 13:37:44 MSK +03:00</code></p>  <p>PS</p>  <p>Rails.version == '4.2.1'</p>